    "summary": "Researcher, based at the Institute for Criminology and Sociology of Law (IKRS) at the University of Oslo.  I have expertise in people-centred and practice-oriented (forced) migration research, humanitarian innovation and gender and intersectionality. \n\nExpert on Jordan and the Middle Eastern refugee protection context. Experience in migration research within and from the African continent (Niger, Zimbabwe, Sudan and Mali). \n\nI am highly skilled in diverse research techniques, some quantitative but in particular qualitative techniques (focus group discussions, participatory action research, visual methods, discourse analysis and content and textual analysis of media texts). I am inspired by feminist and decolonising pedagogical practices. \n\nEfficient, innovative, dedicated, excellent communicator to different audiences (academics, donors, beneficiaries, students). I have the ability to maintain overview without losing attention for details.\n\nMy language skills are: English (Fluent), Dutch (mother tongue), French (reading skills good, speaking skills intermediate), Arabic (intermediate speaking, writing and reading skills).",
