                    "description": "I worked as research consultant for the Project \u201cVoices of African migrants: Identifying best practices for media coverage of migrant issues through content and audience studies\u201d, which was based at the University of Leicester, Leicester, UK with field visits to Niger, Zimbabwe and Morocco. The project was conducted for the Danish NGO International Media Support and funded for by the Ford Foundation. \n\nMain project features: Evaluation of the nature and quality of media stories produced by journalists supported by International Media Support and the reception and responses by local audiences. It used content analysis, interviews and focus group discussions. \n \nResponsibilities performed: Review of literature; discourse, content and textual analysis of media texts (in French and English); Focus Group Discussions and interviews in Niger and Zimbabwe; Thematic analysis of the fieldwork data (using Nvivo). Report writing.",
