                    "company": "University of Leicester",
                    "description": "I obtained my PhD (without corrections) from the School of Media, Communication and Sociology at the University of Leicester. I succesfully defended my PhD-thesis \u201cThe Mediation of Prolonged Displacement in the Everyday Iraqi Refugee Household in Jordan\u201d in December 2017. The thesis drew upon ethnographic research and considered the interplay between living in prolonged legal and social uncertainty and media-use. I argue conflict-affected migrants should be considered as digital connected but also points to the importance for caution for a too celebratory stance towards the \u2018newness\u2019 of digital connections and innovation. Online and offline interpretations of uncertainty in the present occur in reference to the past which includes one\u2019s (prior) socio-historical positioning and in continuation of (neo)colonial, capitalist and patriarchal entanglements. \n\nAs a Graduate Research Assistant I organised workshops and two international conferences, was editor of the postgraduate peer-reviewed journal of the School of Media, Communication and Sociology, was the PhD-representative and helped my PhD-supervisors (Prof. Dr. Leah Bassel and Prof. Dr. Helen Wood) with literature review and some coding and data-analysis for their respective work.",
